  "prompt": "What is an In-Flight Crew Member?",
  "response": "An In-Flight Crew Member refers to personnel who work aboard an aircraft during flight. This typically includes flight attendants and occasionally other specialized staff such as air marshals or medics. Their primary responsibilities are to ensure the safety and comfort of passengers. \n\nFlight attendants, the most common type of In-Flight Crew Members, perform various tasks, including but not limited to:\n\n1. Conducting safety demonstrations and ensuring passengers are aware of emergency procedures.\n2. Providing food and beverage service.\n3. Assisting passengers with seating arrangements, luggage storage, and any inquiries.\n4. Monitoring the cabin for any unusual activities or disturbances.\n5. Responding to medical emergencies and other onboard incidents.\n\nIn-Flight Crew Members undergo extensive training to handle a wide range of scenarios to ensure the safe operation of the flight and welfare of the passengers.",
